name: CT of the Facial Bones
description: CT of the maxillofacial region (e.g. trauma dental pathology). Multiplanar reconstructions often requested.

name: CT of the Sinuses
description: CT of the paranasal sinuses (e.g. sinusitis polyps). Coronal and axial views standard.

name: Non-contrast CT of the Head
description: Axial CT scan of the brain without intravenous contrast. Standard protocol for stroke or trauma evaluation.

name: Contrast-enhanced CT of the Head
description: Axial CT scan of the brain with intravenous contrast. Used for detecting tumors infections or vascular abnormalities.

name: Non-contrast CT of the Chest
description: CT of the thorax without contrast (e.g. pneumonia rib fractures). Limited to pulmonary parenchyma and mediastinum.

name: Contrast-enhanced CT of the Chest
description: CT of the chest with IV contrast (e.g. pulmonary embolism coronary CTA). Includes heart lungs and major vessels.

name: Non-contrast CT of the Cervical Spine
description: CT of the neck (C1-C7) without contrast (e.g. trauma degenerative disease). May include soft tissues if indicated.

name: Non-contrast CT of the Thoracic Spine
description: CT of the mid-back (T1-T12) without contrast (e.g. fractures tumors). Limited to bony structures unless contrast is added.

name: Non-contrast CT of the Lumbar Spine
description: CT of the lower back (L1-S1) without contrast (e.g. sciatica herniated discs). Often paired with myelography if nerve root compression is suspected.

name: CT of the Upper Extremity
description: CT of the arm elbow or shoulder (e.g. fracture tumor). Specify joint or region (e.g. humerus scapula).

name: CT of the Lower Extremity
description: CT of the leg knee or hip (e.g. osteomyelitis stress fractures). Specify joint or region (e.g. femur tibia).

name: Non-contrast CT of the Abdomen
description: CT of the abdomen without contrast (e.g. kidney stones acute pain). May include kidneys liver spleen and pancreas.

name: Contrast-enhanced CT of the Abdomen
description: CT of the abdomen with oral and IV contrast (e.g. bowel obstruction). Enhanced visualization of organs and vasculature.

name: Non-contrast CT of the Pelvis
description: CT of the pelvis without contrast (e.g. hip fractures pelvic masses). Includes pelvic bones bladder and reproductive organs.

name: Contrast-enhanced CT of the Pelvis
description: CT of the pelvis with IV contrast (e.g. ovarian cysts prostate evaluation). Often combined with abdominal CT for comprehensive imaging.

name: CT Colonography (Virtual Colonoscopy)
description: Low-dose CT for colorectal cancer screening. Requires bowel preparation; no sedation needed.

name: CT of the Kidneys
description: Dedicated renal CT with IV contrast (e.g. hydronephrosis renal masses). Includes ureters and bladder if extended.

name: CT of the Pancreas
description: Multiphase pancreatic CT with IV contrast (e.g. pancreatitis cancer). Portal venous phase critical for tumor assessment.

name: CT Angiography of the Chest
description: Dedicated CT angiogram for coronary arteries or pulmonary embolism. Requires rapid IV contrast administration.

name: MRI of the Brain Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the brain without contrast (e.g. MS tumors). Standard protocol for neurological conditions.

name: MRI of the Brain With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the brain with gadolinium contrast (e.g. tumors vasculature). Used for detecting enhancing lesions.

name: MRI of the Brain with and without Contrast
description: Complete MRI of the brain with and without contrast (e.g. comprehensive neuroimaging). Includes both pre- and post-contrast sequences.

name: MRI of the Brain Angiography
description: Dedicated MRA of the brain vessels (e.g. aneurysms AVMs). Requires gadolinium contrast.

name: MRI of the Spine Without Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the cervical spine without contrast (e.g. disc herniation stenosis). Limited to bony structures unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Spine With Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the cervical spine with gadolinium contrast (e.g. spinal cord tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Thoracic Spine Without Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the thoracic spine without contrast (e.g. fractures tumors). Limited to bony structures unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Thoracic Spine With Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the thoracic spine with gadolinium contrast (e.g. spinal cord tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Lumbar Spine Without Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the lumbar spine without contrast (e.g. disc herniation stenosis). Limited to bony structures unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Lumbar Spine With Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the lumbar spine with gadolinium contrast (e.g. spinal cord tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Sacrum and Coccyx Without Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the sacrum and coccyx without contrast (e.g. fractures tumors). Limited to bony structures unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Sacrum and Coccyx With Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the sacrum and coccyx with gadolinium contrast (e.g. spinal cord tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Shoulder Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the shoulder without contrast (e.g. rotator cuff tears labral injuries). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Shoulder With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the shoulder with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Elbow Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the elbow without contrast (e.g. ligament tears fractures). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Elbow With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the elbow with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Wrist Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the wrist without contrast (e.g. fractures carpal tunnel syndrome). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Wrist With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the wrist with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Hip Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the hip without contrast (e.g. labral tears arthritis). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Hip With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the hip with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Knee Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the knee without contrast (e.g. meniscal tears ligament injuries). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Knee With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the knee with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Ankle Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the ankle without contrast (e.g. fractures tendinitis). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Ankle With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the ankle with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Joints of the Hand Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the hand joints without contrast (e.g. arthritis fractures). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Joints of the Hand With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the hand joints with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Joints of the Foot Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the foot joints without contrast (e.g. arthritis fractures). Limited to soft tissues unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Joints of the Foot With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the foot joints with gadolinium contrast (e.g. soft tissue tumors). Enhanced visualization of soft tissues.

name: MRI of the Pelvis Without Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the pelvis without contrast (e.g. hip fractures pelvic masses). Includes pelvic bones bladder and reproductive organs.

name: MRI of the Pelvis With Contrast
description: Axial and sagittal MRI of the pelvis with gadolinium contrast (e.g. ovarian cysts prostate evaluation). Often combined with abdominal MRI for comprehensive imaging.

name: MRI of the Abdomen Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the abdomen without contrast (e.g. liver masses pancreatitis). May include kidneys liver spleen and pancreas.

name: MRI of the Abdomen With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the abdomen with gadolinium contrast (e.g. liver tumors pancreatic cancer). Enhanced visualization of organs and vasculature.

name: MRI of the Liver Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the liver without contrast (e.g. hemangiomas focal nodular hyperplasia). Limited to liver unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Liver With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the liver with gadolinium contrast (e.g. hepatocellular carcinoma metastases). Enhanced visualization of liver lesions.

name: MRI of the Pancreas Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the pancreas without contrast (e.g. chronic pancreatitis pseudocysts). Limited to pancreas unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Pancreas With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the pancreas with gadolinium contrast (e.g. pancreatic cancer cysts). Enhanced visualization of pancreatic lesions.

name: MRI of the Adrenal Glands Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the adrenal glands without contrast (e.g. adenomas pheochromocytomas). Limited to adrenal glands unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Adrenal Glands With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the adrenal glands with gadolinium contrast (e.g. adenomas pheochromocytomas). Enhanced visualization of adrenal lesions.

name: MRI of the Retroperitoneum Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the retroperitoneum without contrast (e.g. lymphadenopathy tumors). Includes retroperitoneal structures.

name: MRI of the Retroperitoneum With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the retroperitoneum with gadolinium contrast (e.g. lymphadenopathy tumors). Enhanced visualization of retroperitoneal structures.

name: MRI of the Renal Vessels Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the renal vessels without contrast (e.g. renal artery stenosis). Limited to renal vessels unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Renal Vessels With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the renal vessels with gadolinium contrast (e.g. renal artery stenosis). Enhanced visualization of renal vessels.

name: MRI of the Mesentery Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the mesentery without contrast (e.g. lymphadenopathy tumors). Includes mesenteric structures.

name: MRI of the Mesentery With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the mesentery with gadolinium contrast (e.g. lymphadenopathy tumors). Enhanced visualization of mesenteric structures.

name: MRI of the Peritoneum Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the peritoneum without contrast (e.g. peritonitis tumors). Includes peritoneal structures.

name: MRI of the Peritoneum With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the peritoneum with gadolinium contrast (e.g. peritonitis tumors). Enhanced visualization of peritoneal structures.

name: MRI of the Prostate Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the prostate without contrast (e.g. benign prostatic hyperplasia). Limited to prostate unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Prostate With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the prostate with gadolinium contrast (e.g. prostate cancer). Enhanced visualization of prostate lesions.

name: MRI of the Uterus Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the uterus without contrast (e.g. fibroids endometriosis). Limited to uterus unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Uterus With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the uterus with gadolinium contrast (e.g. leiomyosarcoma). Enhanced visualization of uterine lesions.

name: MRI of the Ovaries Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the ovaries without contrast (e.g. cysts tumors). Limited to ovaries unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Ovaries With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the ovaries with gadolinium contrast (e.g. ovarian cancer). Enhanced visualization of ovarian lesions.

name: MRI of the Testes Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the testes without contrast (e.g. hydroceles tumors). Limited to testes unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Testes With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the testes with gadolinium contrast (e.g. testicular cancer). Enhanced visualization of testicular lesions.

name: MRI of the Breast Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the breast without contrast (e.g. breast cancer screening). Used for high-risk patients or dense breasts.

name: MRI of the Breast With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the breast with gadolinium contrast (e.g. breast cancer diagnosis). Enhanced visualization of breast lesions.

name: MRI of the Chest Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the chest without contrast (e.g. pulmonary fibrosis mediastinal masses). Includes lungs mediastinum and great vessels.

name: MRI of the Chest With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the chest with gadolinium contrast (e.g. lung cancer mediastinal tumors). Enhanced visualization of chest structures.

name: MRI of the Heart Without Contrast
description: Axial and short-axis MRI of the heart without contrast (e.g. congenital heart disease valve disorders). Limited to cardiac structures unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Heart With Contrast
description: Axial and short-axis MRI of the heart with gadolinium contrast (e.g. myocardial perfusion infarction). Enhanced visualization of cardiac structures.

name: MRI of the Coronary Arteries Without Contrast
description: Axial and short-axis MRI of the coronary arteries without contrast (e.g. coronary artery disease). Limited to coronary arteries unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Coronary Arteries With Contrast
description: Axial and short-axis MRI of the coronary arteries with gadolinium contrast (e.g. coronary artery disease). Enhanced visualization of coronary arteries.

name: MRI of the Aorta Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the aorta without contrast (e.g. aneurysms dissections). Limited to aorta unless contrast is added.

name: MRI of the Aorta With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the aorta with gadolinium contrast (e.g. aortic aneurysms dissections). Enhanced visualization of aortic structures.

name: MRI of the Neck Without Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the neck without contrast (e.g. thyroid nodules lymph nodes). Includes thyroid parathyroid and lymph nodes.

name: MRI of the Neck With Contrast
description: Axial and coronal MRI of the neck with gadolinium contrast (e.g. thyroid cancer lymph node metastasis). Enhanced visualization of neck structures.

name: Basic Metabolic Panel (BMP)
description: Evaluates electrolytes kidney function and blood sugar levels.

name: Comprehensive Metabolic Panel (CMP)
description: Expands on BMP by adding liver function tests and lipid profile.

name: Lipid Panel
description: Measures cholesterol triglycerides HDL and LDL levels to assess cardiovascular risk.

name: Liver Function Tests
description: Evaluates liver health by measuring enzymes like ALT AST and bilirubin.

name: Kidney Function Tests
description: Assesses kidney function by measuring creatinine BUN and electrolytes.

name: Complete Blood Count (CBC)
description: Measures red blood cells white blood cells platelets hemoglobin and hematocrit levels.

name: Hemoglobin A1c (HbA1c)
description: Assesses average blood glucose levels over 2-3 months for diabetes monitoring.

name: Platelet Count
description: Determines the number of platelets in the blood to assess clotting ability.

name: White Blood Cell (WBC) Count
description: Measures white blood cells to detect infections inflammation or immune disorders.

name: Erythrocyte Sedimentation Rate (ESR)
description: Measures inflammation by tracking the rate at which red blood cells settle in plasma.

name: Antinuclear Antibody (ANA) Test
description: Detects autoantibodies that target nuclear components often used in diagnosing autoimmune diseases.

name: Rheumatoid Factor (RF) Test
description: Measures rheumatoid factor antibodies associated with rheumatoid arthritis.

name: Thyroid-Stimulating Hormone (TSH) Test
description: Evaluates thyroid function by measuring TSH levels indicating hypothyroidism or hyperthyroidism.

name: HIV Antibody Test
description: Detects antibodies against HIV used for diagnosing HIV infection.

name: Hepatitis C Antibody Test
description: Identifies antibodies against the hepatitis C virus used for diagnosing hepatitis C infection.

name: Culture and Sensitivity Testing
description: Identifies bacteria or fungi in a sample and determines antibiotic susceptibility.

name: Urine Culture
description: Detects bacterial or fungal infections in urine commonly used for urinary tract infections.

name: Stool Culture
description: Identifies pathogens in stool samples useful for diagnosing gastrointestinal infections.

name: Sputum Culture
description: Analyzes sputum samples to identify respiratory pathogens such as bacteria or fungi.

name: Blood Culture
description: Detects bloodstream infections by identifying bacteria or fungi in blood samples.

name: BRCA1/BRCA2 Mutation Analysis
description: Detects mutations in the BRCA1 and BRCA2 genes used in breast and ovarian cancer screening.

name: EGFR Mutation Analysis
description: Identifies mutations in the EGFR gene used in non-small cell lung cancer treatment.

name: KRAS Mutation Analysis
description: Detects mutations in the KRAS gene used in colorectal and pancreatic cancer treatment.

name: ALK Rearrangement Analysis
description: Identifies ALK rearrangements used in non-small cell lung cancer treatment.

name: HER2 Amplification Analysis
description: Detects HER2 gene amplification used in breast cancer treatment.

name: NGS Panel for Cancer Genes
description: Comprehensive next-generation sequencing panel for multiple cancer-related genes.

name: Cystic Fibrosis Gene Mutation Analysis
description: Detects mutations in the CFTR gene used in cystic fibrosis diagnosis.

name: HPV DNA Test
description: Identifies human papillomavirus DNA used in cervical cancer screening.

name: HLA Typing
description: Determines human leukocyte antigen types used in organ transplantation and hematopoietic stem cell transplantation.

name: SARS-CoV-2 PCR Test
description: Detects SARS-CoV-2 RNA used in COVID-19 diagnosis.
